> I think we should build CBMC from source as well to have an easier time updating the version as the CBMC responds to issues we find (Rod has already reported a few things I think).

@potsrevennil points out that this is going to be easy by using `pkgs.cbmc.overrideAttrs` with a new version or commit hash from the repo. You can ping us once you actually need a newer version and we can change it. We won't need to write our own build script. 

We've done something similar for astyle as the most recent version is buggy: https://github.com/mkannwischer/mlkem-c-aarch64/blob/d9f9300c52f1e38aea1a172916edf80aa9ca0eca/flake.nix#L23
